	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Senator in 43? He was Suetonius' authority for a dispute in the Senate between Octavian and Lepidus about the proscriptions (Suet. Aug. 27.2). Munzer (RE) considers him a senator. See Wiseman, CQ 14, 1964, 124.\n" .
